Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.98,0:01:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- Things aren't looking good, Oz.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.68,0:01:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ever the optimist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.52,0:01:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,While I would not say our\Ncurrents predicaments is ideal,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.61,0:01:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we can both agree
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.87,0:01:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that the situation could be much worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.23,0:01:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Humanity is a resilient force.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.36,0:01:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oz, pro huntsmen like that\Ndon't just bite it all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.47,0:02:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Salem's powerful, and\Nit seems like her reach
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.33,0:02:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is growing by the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.87,0:02:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that say about humanity?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.03,0:02:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- That there are indeed a misguided few
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.34,0:02:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who have filled their hearts with malice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.18,0:02:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't take a great number\Nof people to cause harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.45,0:02:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But I still believe there are\Nfar more people in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.63,0:02:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,willing to prevent it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.29,0:02:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.43,0:02:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ah, Miss Rose, join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.12,0:02:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We were just about to gather everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.83,0:02:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to discuss our next steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.27,0:02:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, great.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.68,0:02:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- Something on your mind, kiddo?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.24,0:02:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- If it's okay to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.20,0:02:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.55,0:02:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, we've been talking\Nabout the relic in Haven,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.16,0:02:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Spring Maiden but,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.60,0:02:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what about the Fall Maiden?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.98,0:02:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- Cinder?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.22,0:03:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- Does that mean Salem\Nhas the Beacon relic?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.69,0:03:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- Very astute, Miss Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.10,0:03:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wondering who would\Nbe the first to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.49,0:03:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thankfully, she does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.31,0:03:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that the relic at\NHaven is very much at risk,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.69,0:03:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and for now that should\Nremain our primary focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.88,0:03:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just say I made\Nfinding the relic at Beacon
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.04,0:03:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a bit more challenging\Nthan at the other schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.08,0:03:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, that's good hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.25,0:03:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- It is, but let's not\Nforget the challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.41,0:03:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that still lie before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.86,0:03:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, is there anything\Nelse we can help you with?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.82,0:03:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, I did have one more question.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.19,0:03:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, my cane is not a relic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.01,0:03:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- I have no more questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.50,0:04:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes, while this cane is\Nindeed very precious to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.40,0:04:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it is also just that, precious to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.02,0:04:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,While I admit it still has a\Nfew more tricks up its sleeve,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.21,0:04:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I can firmly say that being\Na relic isn't one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.53,0:04:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why don't you run and\Nget the other students?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.42,0:04:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.32,0:04:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.21,0:04:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we'll be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.09,0:04:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Rose] Who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.17,0:04:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- (sighs) It was Leo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.64,0:04:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Says he had a breakthrough\Nwith the council.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.54,0:04:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinks he might be able to get together
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.21,0:04:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,a small raiding party for the bandits.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.13,0:04:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants us to meet up at\Nthe school tomorrow night
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.53,0:04:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to walk us through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.03,0:04:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- Really, oh that's great,\NI'll go get the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.68,0:05:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hm, that sounds drastically different
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.99,0:05:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,from your original\Nconversation, does it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.78,0:05:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- It does.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.18,0:05:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.71,0:05:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- Things aren't looking good, Oz.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.27,0:05:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.25,0:05:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- I still have questions for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.58,0:05:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're not alone in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.58,0:05:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- You know, I never expected\Nyou would be the one
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.12,0:05:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to have the guts to betray Oz.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.89,0:05:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Which makes me wonder,\Nwhat does she have on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.18,0:05:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm helping her for\Nthe same reason you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.35,0:05:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.67,0:05:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We, we can't stop her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.42,0:05:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No one can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.29,0:05:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's why I tried to leave when I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.29,0:05:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not afraid, I'm smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.77,0:05:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- You can call it whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.26,0:06:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't really matter,\Nwe are here, helping her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.19,0:06:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I've crossed a line.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.24,0:06:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done things that\NOzpin will never forgive,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.19,0:06:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and he shouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.23,0:06:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where I go from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.79,0:06:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- Man up, you did what\Nyou had to do to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.64,0:06:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no shame in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.06,0:06:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- Who are you trying to convince?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.86,0:06:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- Do you have a better idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.38,0:07:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- Quiet now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.60,0:07:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.34,0:07:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Blake] Did you come in here to hide?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.55,0:07:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- I told you, I didn't want this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.61,0:07:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- But you're still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.49,0:07:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.16,0:07:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- Of course you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.27,0:07:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Just stay out of my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.97,0:07:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why do you feel like\Nwe have to hurt people
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:07:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to get our way?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.90,0:08:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- Because it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.60,0:08:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- That doesn't make it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.33,0:08:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ilia] Stop lecturing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.17,0:08:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ilia] Why couldn't you just leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.49,0:08:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- Because I run away too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.13,0:08:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sorry, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.19,0:09:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- Quit taking pot shots, and\Nfight me like you mean it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.02,0:09:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You used to see things the\Nway I did, the way Adam did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.81,0:09:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If no one's going to do anything
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.51,0:09:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop the humans that attack us,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.82,0:09:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then the only choice we\Nhave left is to attack back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.21,0:10:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're wrong there's\Nalways another choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.25,0:10:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ilia, please, you're a good person,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.87,0:10:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're making all the wrong decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.37,0:10:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.35,0:10:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- Is this really what your\Nparents would have wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.87,0:10:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't know what else to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.40,0:10:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what else to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.42,0:10:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- Blake!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.55,0:10:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.25,0:11:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ilia, what you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.20,0:11:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.74,0:11:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.27,0:11:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- Go help Blake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.69,0:11:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- On it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.88,0:12:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.41,0:12:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.67,0:12:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- Move, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Blake] Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.51,0:13:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- What have you done?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.67,0:13:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You ruined everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.03,0:13:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.50,0:14:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Back, everyone, stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.39,0:14:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got people inside doing their best.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.65,0:14:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.76,0:14:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- Get in there, search for any stragglers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.62,0:14:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We came as soon as we got the call.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.94,0:14:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And Finnick?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.60,0:14:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it worth it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.12,0:15:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- Blake!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.49,0:15:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- Humans didn't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.20,0:15:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.33,0:15:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Faunus.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.36,0:15:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We did this to ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.01,0:15:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just as capable of hate\Nand violence as the humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.29,0:15:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't think any of\Nus would jump at the chance
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.44,0:15:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to point that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.81,0:15:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So why are we letting Adam do it for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.20,0:15:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,By doing nothing and staying silent,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.94,0:15:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we let others speak and act in our place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.85,0:15:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we're not proud\Nof the choices they make,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.48,0:15:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,then we have no one to\Nblame but ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.38,0:16:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the message Adam\NTaurus will bring to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.12,0:16:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,if no one stops him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.08,0:16:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.10,0:16:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to understand\Nthat all of you are looking
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.87,0:16:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for simple answers to a\Nvery complicated problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.57,0:16:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can't give that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.76,0:16:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to make\Nhate go away, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.49,0:16:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know that this kind of\Nviolence is not the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.33,0:16:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that to ask\Nyou to leave your homes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.57,0:16:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and protect Haven Academy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.35,0:16:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is asking you to put your lives at risk,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.67,0:16:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's what's at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.78,0:16:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going, and I'll stand\Nby myself, if I have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.69,0:16:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll stand with you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.09,0:17:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If, if you'd have me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.89,0:17:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- Isn't that the White Fang Girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.13,0:17:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- I thought she hated the Belladonnas.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.04,0:17:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're not going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.64,0:17:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Blake] Let her come.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.51,0:17:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.73,0:17:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just going to forgive her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.78,0:17:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,After everything she did?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.33,0:17:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.35,0:17:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- What does she think she's doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.73,0:17:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- She's learned a lesson that evaded me
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.88,0:17:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,until I was much older.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.16,0:17:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That there is strength in forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.40,0:17:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Mata] I'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.28,0:17:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll go, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.57,0:17:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Crowd] I'll stand with\Nyou, yeah, me too, me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.89,0:18:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Looks like we've got work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.48,0:18:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.44,0:18:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- You stabbed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.62,0:18:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.56,0:18:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- There, let's just call it even.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.26,0:18:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- We have about two weeks\Nbefore Adam's attack on Haven.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.88,0:18:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to need shields, and training,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.12,0:18:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever we can do to protect\Nas many people as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.80,0:18:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- We'll need transportation,\Ntoo, for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.33,0:18:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- I think I know a ship\Ncaptain who owes us a favor.
